        <h2>EFFECTS</h2>
        <p>  Developing intoxication detection software via facial expressions and body movements enhances safety for law enforcement and venues but demands accuracy to distinguish behaviors accurately. Privacy concerns arise due to monitoring, requiring ethical deployment and regulations. Potential positive effects include preventing accidents and promoting responsible drinking, yet technical limitations and societal impact necessitate careful consideration for responsible use and societal acceptance. </p>
