      <section id="prevention">
        <!-- Homepage Content -->
        <h2>PREVENTIONS</h2>
        <p> <b>Education:</b> Raise awareness about the dangers of drink driving through campaigns and educational programs.

            <b>Enforcement:</b> Implement strict laws and penalties for drink driving to deter individuals from engaging in this behavior.
            
            <b>Alternative Transportation:</b>Promote and facilitate access to safe transportation options like taxis, rideshare services, or designated drivers.
            
            <b>Technological Solutions:</b> Use breathalyzer ignition locks or apps that estimate blood alcohol content to discourage driving under the influence.
            
            <b>Community Involvement:</b> Encourage community involvement in preventing drink driving through initiatives and support groups.
            
            <b>Responsible Serving: </b>Train bartenders and staff to recognize signs of intoxication and limit alcohol consumption in bars and venues.
            
            <b>Personal Responsibility:</b> Encourage individuals to plan ahead, designate a sober driver, or use alternative transportation before drinking.
            
           <b>Peer Influence: </b>Foster a culture where friends and peers discourage drink driving and intervene if someone is unfit to drive.
            
            <b>Regulation and Policies:</b> Support and enforce policies aimed at reducing alcohol availability and promoting responsible consumption.
            
            <b>Continuous Evaluation:</b> Regularly assess and improve prevention strategies based on effectiveness and changing trends.</p>
        <!-- Image -->
      
        <img src="PREVENTION.jpg" alt="Drink Driving Image"width="300" height="200">>
